---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const images = [
  '/wordstash/image1.png',
  '/wordstash/image2.png',
  '/wordstash/image3.png',
  '/wordstash/image4.png',
];
---

<Layout title="WordStash - Your Personal Vocabulary Companion">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <!-- Back Button -->
    <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center text-purple-400 hover:text-purple-300 mb-8 transition-colors">
      <svg class="w-5 h-5 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 19l-7-7m0 0l7-7m-7 7h18" />
      </svg>
      Back to Apps
    </a>

    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <div class="text-6xl mb-6">📚</div>
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold mb-4 bg-clip-text text-transparent bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-400 to-cyan-400">
        WordStash
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-slate-300 mb-6">
        Your Personal Vocabulary Companion
      </p>
      <div class="flex justify-center gap-4 mb-6">
        <span class="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-500/20 text-blue-300 rounded-full text-sm border border-blue-500/30">
          📱 iOS App
        </span>
        <span class="px-4 py-2 bg-green-500/20 text-green-300 rounded-full text-sm border border-green-500/30">
          ✓ Published
        </span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Screenshots -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-16">
      {images.map((src) => (
        <div class="rounded-xl overflow-hidden border border-slate-700 bg-slate-800/50">
          <img 
            src={src} 
            alt="WordStash Screenshot" 
            class="w-full h-auto"
            onerror="this.parentElement.innerHTML='<div class=\'aspect-[9/16] flex items-center justify-center text-slate-600\'>Screenshot Coming Soon</div>'"
          />
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <!-- Blog Content -->
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none">
      <div class="bg-slate-800/30 backdrop-blur-sm border border-slate-700 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-purple-400">Introducing WordStash</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
          I've always loved learning new words. Whether it's stumbling upon an interesting term while reading, 
          or hearing someone use a word I've never encountered before, I wanted a simple way to capture and 
          remember these vocabulary gems.
        </p>
        <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mt-4">
          That's why I built <strong class="text-white">WordStash</strong> – a dead-simple vocabulary app that  makes building your word collection effortless.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-slate-800/30 backdrop-blur-sm border border-slate-700 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-purple-400">The Problem I Wanted to Solve</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
          You know that moment when you're reading on your phone and come across a word you don't know? 
          You could switch apps, look it up, maybe save it somewhere... but honestly, it's too much friction. 
          By the time you get back to reading, you've lost your flow.
        </p>
        <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mt-4">
          I wanted something faster. Something that just works.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-slate-800/30 backdrop-blur-sm border border-slate-700 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-purple-400">How It Works</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          WordStash is built around one simple idea: <strong class="text-white">capturing words should take seconds, not minutes.</strong>
        </p>
        <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">Here's my typical workflow:</p>
        <ol class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed space-y-2 ml-6">
          <li>See a new word while reading</li>
          <li>Copy it</li>
          <li>Open WordStash and tap the clipboard button</li>
          <li>Done.</li>
        </ol>
        <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mt-4">
          The app automatically fetches the meaning and usage examples using AI. No typing, no searching – just instant knowledge.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-slate-800/30 backdrop-blur-sm border border-slate-700 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-purple-400">Features I'm Proud Of</h2>
        
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-400 mb-2">1. AI-Powered Definitions</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
              Every word you add gets an automatic definition and real-world usage examples. 
              I integrated OpenAI's API to make this happen, and the results are impressively accurate.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-400 mb-2">2. Pronunciation Made Easy</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
              Tap the speaker icon next to any word and hear how it's pronounced. No need for phonetic symbols – 
              just tap and listen. This uses iOS's built-in text-to-speech, so it works offline and supports multiple languages.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-400 mb-2">3. Flash Cards for Review</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
              Learning words is one thing, <em>remembering</em> them is another. I added swipeable flash cards 
              with smooth flip animations. You can filter to review just your starred words, perfect for exam prep 
              or focused study sessions.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-400 mb-2">4. Cloud Sync</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
              Your vocabulary collection syncs across all your devices using Supabase. Start building your list 
              on your iPhone, review it on your iPad – everything stays in sync.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-400 mb-2">5. Beautiful Design</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
              I went for a clean, modern interface with glassmorphic cards and smooth animations. 
              No clutter, no distractions – just your words and their meanings.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-slate-800/30 backdrop-blur-sm border border-slate-700 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-purple-400">The Tech Stack</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">For fellow developers curious about what's under the hood:</p>
        <ul class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed space-y-2 ml-6">
          <li><strong class="text-white">SwiftUI</strong> for the interface</li>
          <li><strong class="text-white">SwiftData</strong> for local storage</li>
          <li><strong class="text-white">Supabase</strong> for authentication and cloud sync</li>
          <li><strong class="text-white">OpenAI API</strong> for AI-generated definitions</li>
          <li><strong class="text-white">AVSpeechSynthesizer</strong> for pronunciation</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mt-4">
          Everything is built with iOS 17 in mind, taking advantage of the latest SwiftUI features.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-slate-800/30 backdrop-blur-sm border border-slate-700 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-purple-400">Who It's For</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">WordStash is perfect if you:</p>
        <ul class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed space-y-2 ml-6">
          <li>Love reading and encounter new words regularly</li>
          <li>Are studying for standardized tests (SAT, GRE, TOEFL)</li>
          <li>Want to improve your professional vocabulary</li>
          <li>Are learning English as a second language</li>
          <li>Just enjoy learning new words</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-900/30 to-cyan-900/30 backdrop-blur-sm border border-blue-500/30 rounded-2xl p-8 text-center">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-blue-400">Built During My Hospital Stay</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
          This app was created in just 1 day during my 5-day hospital stay, using AI-driven development. 
          It's a testament to what's possible when you combine clear vision with modern development tools.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <div class="mt-16 text-center">
      <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-500 to-cyan-500 text-white rounded-lg hover:from-blue-600 hover:to-cyan-600 transition-all">
        <svg class="w-5 h-5 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 19l-7-7m0 0l7-7m-7 7h18" />
        </svg>
        Back to All Apps
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
